<subsection xml:id="subsec-Suitable-scale-for-graphs-of-data">
    <title>Suitable scale for graphs of data</title>
     <activity>
        <p>
            work in groups
        </p>
        <p>
            (i) consider the table below
        </p>
        <table>
            <title></title>
            <tabular left="medium" right="medium" top="medium" bottom="medium">
                <row halign="left" header="yes">
                    <cell>Marks</cell>
                    <cell>Frequency</cell>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <cell>4</cell>
                    <cell>2</cell>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <cell>5</cell>
                    <cell>10</cell>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <cell>6</cell>
                    <cell>5</cell>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <cell>7</cell>
                    <cell>20</cell>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <cell>8</cell>
                    <cell>3</cell>
                </row>
                <row>
                    <cell>9</cell>
                    <cell>4</cell>
                </row>
            </tabular>
        </table>
        <p>
            (ii) Determine a suitable scale you would use to draw a bar graph.
        </p>
        <p>
            (iii) Discuss and compare with other groups.
        </p>
    </activity>

     <p>
        Learning point
    </p>
    <p>
        <ul>
            <li>
                <p>
                     A suitable scale should be chosen in such a way that data is easy to plot and easy to read.
                </p>
            </li>
        </ul>
    </p>
        
   </subsection>